SyslogFacility AUTHPRIV
AuthorizedKeysFile  .ssh/authorized_keys
UsePrivilegeSeparation sandbox # Default for new installations.
AcceptEnv LANG LC_*
Subsystem   sftp    /usr/libexec/sftp-server
please note that the /etc/passwd file is a system file, and modifying it can have unintended consequences. It is recommended to avoid making changes to this file without proper understanding and caution.Apologies for the confusion. The /etc/passwd file typically contains entries for user accounts on a Unix-like system, and it may not have the pattern "bin" in every line. If you're looking to exclude lines containing the word "bin" in the /etc/passwd file, you can use the grep command with the -v option and specify a pattern that matches the entire line.
